<br />
And we have always relied on single pulls for the most part...</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I disagree...  with npc target toggling and a low mana root, would make adds trivial.  I can see if root breaks untimely this could be a problem, but this is something every class with root deals with.  
<br />

<br />
Rangers root park adds while continuing to give dps to the main mob, clerics root park adds while healing and shamans root park adds while slowing etc...  
<br />

<br />
I don't want root, but I do feel that it would add a good chunk of utility to mages.  /shrug</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
