			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Im not sure what you hunt or where Naladini but i hunt very well in places like dungeons and do not need to hunt in places where i can 'safely' pull. (of course this can be in dungeons and outdoor zones)
<br />

<br />
For me (and this is my opinion) i like the challenge of doing what is not 'safe' and the 'usual' thing with my character. Learning new skills and tricks (some gleaned from these boards!) has given me a new lease of life on my character. Heck, i walk into places now and apply those tactics despite people i know saying 'you will die there' 'your class cannot solo there' and so on. Then they congratulate me on not only surviving, but expanding further into the zone with abandon (see my latest post on Hate)
<br />

<br />
I think too many people see individual classes doing extraordinary things and say to themselves, if only they gave that to us. Our class can, and does, wonderful things, both solo and in groups. At the end of the day, its what you want out of the game and what your prepared to put into it, be it time or effort. I personally do not raid, and i am not guilded, yet i farm plat, loot, and do multiple quests for my char or alts and i have never once said to myself, if only i could do that (kill a certain mob, go to a certain place, get a certain peice of loot) all because of limitations on my class of character.
<br />

<br />
At the end of the day, i think our class is good all around. There are some minor points I would like cleaned up (lore off summoned items, haste mask upgraded and added to say, summoned belt) but when peeps ask for root and snare and such, i believe they dont want a mage to be better, they want a mage to be a self contained group in one character.<br />_________________<br />With an awesome array of destructive pets and the power at your fingertips to scorch the earth, who can doubt the true power of the magician.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
