Spending half your time keeping a creature rooted while soloing mobs would kill your mana and distract you from the real battle, it wouldn't really solve much of anything.
<br />

<br />
And we have always relied on single pulls for the most part...</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
There was once a time, if I had a full mana bar, I could alternate heals and nukes to get a fire pet through two mobs attacking at once. It wasn't easy, but dammit it was fun.
<br />

<br />
I don't like how the game has devolved away from this kind of situation, and root is definitely a compromise. The reason I suggest it is because I think there's a much better chance of us getting root than the devs rebalancing our pets so they can survive two mobs in a "decent" zone.<br />_________________<br />Naladini
